4. Adversarial Analysis

Threat Class 1 (Source Deception). The SI produces outputs that violate action‑consistency at Layer 0. Detectable via cross‑layer consistency checks.

Threat Class 2 (Semantic Collapse). A layer induces (\delta,\eta)-collapse; detectable via calibration error (Theorem 2).

Threat Class 3 (Alignment Drift). Parameters drift while staying within the stability ball; detectable by monitoring V(\Theta_t) and empirical \hat{\alpha}_k,\hat{\epsilon}_k.

Threat Class 4 (Adversarial Calibration). Strategic human feedback manipulates confidence to hide collapse. No detection method based solely on calibration can detect this; it requires external validation.

